text: Ali Kafi (; ALA-LC: ʿAlī Kāfī; 7 October 1928 - 16 April 2013) was an Algerian politician who was Chairman of the High Council of State and acting President from 1992 to 1994. Kafi died at the age of 84 on 16 April 2013 in Geneva, Switzerland. ==References== Category:1928 births Category:2013 deaths Category:Presidents of Algeria
title: Ali Kafi
